The Chinese Children's Center will hold a series of activities to allow children to experience high technology during the "June 1" (Children's Day) - Xinhua.
Xinhua News Agency Beijing, May 20th (Reporters Huang Xiaoxi and Zhou Shan Shan): The China Children's Center informed on the 20th that during and after the "June 1st" Children's Day from May 28th to June 1st, a series of activities such as child maker experience, child visual art festival, and parent-child book fragrance carnival will be held by the China Children's Center, allowing children to spend the "June 1st" in the charm of cutting-edge technology.
It is understood that the activities held by Chinese Children's Center during this year's Children's Day include "Loving Family Creates Coolness" Children's Future Learning Carnival, the First Children's Visual Art Festival, "Fragrance of Books" Activity, "Family Love Reading" Picture Book Series Activities, etc.
Li Zhongming, the Deputy Director of the China Children's Center, said at the 2016 “June 1” Children's Day Media Open Day held on the 20th that "Love Home Creative Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival is the key activity for celebrating “June 1” this year at the China Children's Center.
The activity focuses on integrating social innovation and family individual creativity, allowing children and families to participate in various innovative education activities and making innovation practice into the culture of ordinary families, so that "doing it yourself" will become a new way of learning and life for families.
It is reported that "Ai Jia Chuang Ku" Children's Future Learning Carnival includes dozens of cutting-edge technology experience contents such as the "Douguo Chuang Ke" experience activities, Laoniu Children's Exploration Museum's annual anniversary and "Family Love Exploration for Children Meng Birthday" activities, VR Universal Experience Plan, "Chuang Ke Tribe" interactive workshops, etc.
